The paper focuses on robot manipulation, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of tactile sensing for perceiving clutter and maneuvering within it suggests a potential application of computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The approach to manipulation emphasizes the benefits of making contact across the entire manipulator, which could involve machine learning (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG) techniques. The novel controller presented in the paper also suggests a potential application of control theory (cs.SY).
